Matsushita Electric's battery unit to boost output 
Matsushita Electric Industrial Co. Ltd. said Monday its battery unit
would boost output of titanium lithium ion batteries to 2.7 million
units by the end of March 1997 from 300,000 in the year to March 1996.
Matsushita Battery Industrial Co. Ltd., owned 96.8 percent by the
world's largest consumer electronics company, will export the output to
Europe, aiming at a 10 percent market share worldwide over the next
several years, company officials said.
Titanium lithium ion batteries are used as back-up batteries for solar
powered watches, the officials said.
